{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6b1e93c8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s406"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"406"},"text":"§ 406.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Penalty for wrongful construction of bridges, piers, etc.; removal of structures","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Every person and every corporation that shall violate any of the provisions of sections 401, 403, and 404 of this title or any rule or regulation made by the Secretary of the Army in pursuance of the provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s404"},"text":"section 404 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall be deemed guilty of a misdemeanor, and on conviction thereof shall be punished by a fine not exceeding $2,500 nor less than $500, or by imprisonment (in the case of a natural person) not exceeding one year, or by both such punishments, in the discretion of the court. And further, the removal of any structures or parts of structures erected in violation of the provisions of the said sections may be enforced by the injunction of any district court exercising jurisdiction in any district in which such structures may exist, and proper proceedings to this end may be instituted under the direction of the Attorney General of the United States."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6b1e93c9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1899-03-03/ch425/s12"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1899, ch. 425, § 12","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/30/1151"},"text":"30 Stat. 1151","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1900-02-20/ch23/s2"},"text":"Feb. 20, 1900, ch. 23, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/32"},"text":"31 Stat. 32","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s291"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 291","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1167"},"text":"36 Stat. 1167","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343"},"text":"July 26, 1947, ch. 343","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 205(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6b1e93ca-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6b1e93cb-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id6b1e93cc-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is from act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1899-03-03"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1899","children":[],"tail":", popularly known as the “Rivers and Harbors Appropriation Act of 1899”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id6b1e93cd-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1911—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1911-03-03"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911","children":[],"tail":", transferred to the District Courts the enforcement powers formerly lodged in the Circuit Courts."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1900—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1900-02-20"},"text":"Feb. 20, 1900","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section eleven” for “section fourteen” where first appearing, which for codification purposes, was translated as “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s404"},"text":"section 404 of this title","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id6b1e93ce-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id6b1e93cf-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Department of War designated Department of the Army and title of Secretary of War changed to Secretary of the Army by section 205(a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343/tII"},"text":"act July 26, 1947, ch. 343, title II","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":". Section 205(a) of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1947","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by section 53 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/641"},"text":"70A Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":". Section 1 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956","children":[],"tail":", enacted “Title 10, Armed Forces” which in sections 3010 to 3013 continued Department of the Army under administrative supervision of Secretary of the Army."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id6b1e93d0-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions, powers, and duties of Secretary of the Army and other offices and officers of Department of the Army under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s401"},"text":"section 401 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to extent that they relate generally to location and clearances of bridges and causeways in navigable waters of United States transferred to and vested in Secretary of Transportation by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/670/s6/g/6/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–670, § 6(g)(6)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/941"},"text":"80 Stat. 941","children":[],"tail":", which created Department of Transportation. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/449"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–449","children":[],"tail":" amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s401"},"text":"section 401 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to reflect transfer made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/670/s6/g/6/A"},"text":"section 6(g)(6)(A) of Pub. L. 89–670","children":[],"tail":", and repealed section 6(g)(6)(A)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
